
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hbpldecode` baraye decode kardan file-haye HBPL (HP Basic Language) estefade mishavad. HBPL zaban barname nevisi est ke ghadeeman dar mashin hesab-ha va computer-haye HP estefade mishod. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ke code-haye HBPL ra be shekle ghabl-khani dar biavarid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `hbpldecode filename.hbpl` --> 📑 Decode kardan file `filename.hbpl` va chap kardan natije dar terminal.
    🔹 `hbpldecode -o output.txt filename.hbpl` --> 💾 Decode kardan file `filename.hbpl` va zakhire kardan natije dar file `output.txt`.
    🔹 `hbpldecode -v filename.hbpl` --> 📢 Namayesh etela'at bishtar dar morede process decode kardan (verbose mode).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hbpldecode myprogram.hbpl

    🔹 Decode kardan file `myprogram.hbpl` va chap kardan code decode shode dar terminal.

    $ hbpldecode -o decoded_program.txt myprogram.hbpl

    🔹 Decode kardan file `myprogram.hbpl` va zakhire kardan code decode shode dar file `decoded_program.txt`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hbpldecode -v myprogram.hbpl

    🔹 In dastoor file `myprogram.hbpl` ra decode mikonad va hamzaman etela'at bishtari dar morede process decode kardan namayesh midahad. In komak mikonad agar moshkeli dar decode kardan vojood dashte bashad, on ra peyda konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hbpldecode` command is used to decode HBPL (HP Basic Language) files. HBPL is a programming language formerly used in HP calculators and computers. This command allows you to convert HBPL code into a readable format.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `hbpldecode filename.hbpl` --> 📑 Decode the file `filename.hbpl` and print the result to the terminal.
    🔹 `hbpldecode -o output.txt filename.hbpl` --> 💾 Decode the file `filename.hbpl` and save the result to the file `output.txt`.
    🔹 `hbpldecode -v filename.hbpl` --> 📢 Display more information about the decoding process (verbose mode).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hbpldecode myprogram.hbpl

    🔹 Decode the file `myprogram.hbpl` and print the decoded code to the terminal.

    $ hbpldecode -o decoded_program.txt myprogram.hbpl

    🔹 Decode the file `myprogram.hbpl` and save the decoded code to the file `decoded_program.txt`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hbpldecode -v myprogram.hbpl

    🔹 This command decodes the file `myprogram.hbpl` and simultaneously displays more information about the decoding process. This helps to identify any issues during decoding.
